# A4mask
y_coords, x_coords = np.where(a4_mask > 0)

# 4
top_left = [x_coords[np.argmin(x_coords + y_coords)], y_coords[np.argmin(x_coords + y_coords)]]  # x+y
top_right = [x_coords[np.argmax(x_coords - y_coords)], y_coords[np.argmax(x_coords - y_coords)]]  # x-y
bottom_left = [x_coords[np.argmin(x_coords - y_coords)], y_coords[np.argmin(x_coords - y_coords)]]  # x-y
bottom_right = [x_coords[np.argmax(x_coords + y_coords)], y_coords[np.argmax(x_coords + y_coords)]]  # x+y

# 
corners = np.array([top_left, top_right, bottom_right, bottom_left], dtype=np.float32)

print("A44:")
corner_names = ['', '', '', '']
for corner, name in zip(corners, corner_names):
    print(f"  {name}: ({corner[0]:.1f}, {corner[1]:.1f})")

# 
new_width = 420
new_height = int(new_width * 29.7 / 21)  # A4

# 
dst_corners = np.array([
    [0, 0],
    [new_width - 1, 0],
    [new_width - 1, new_height - 1],
    [0, new_height - 1]
], dtype=np.float32)

# 
transform_matrix = cv2.getPerspectiveTransform(corners, dst_corners)
warped_image = cv2.warpPerspective(a4_mask, transform_matrix, (new_width, new_height))

# 
warped_image_bgr = cv2.cvtColor(warped_image, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)
warped_a4_path="result\warped_a4.png"  # 
cv2.imwrite(warped_a4_path, warped_image_bgr)
print(" warped_a4.png")
